latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I’ve always admired Aloe Vera for its capabilities but never found a product where its properties really shone. I recently came across @sadhev aloe vera gel and it definitely changed my views. It’s infused with saffron and Kumkumadi Tailam, both of which are great for addressing a host of skin concerns like blemishes and uneven skin tone. This is a 100% natural gel, perfectly suited for sensitive skin and it smells divine!

It’s really lightweight, absorbs super fast and leaves skin hydrated and plump! I love that it doesn’t slip all over the place like usual Aloe Vera gels which is one of the reasons my Aloe Vera usage has been very limited. Thankfully this isn’t messy or slippery at all.
I personally enjoy slathering it on after I shoot in the sun when my skin feels very sensitive. The Sadhev Aloe Vera Gel always calms it down. Sometimes, I incorporate it in my PM routine too for some over-night repair.

Sadhev sources the ingredients from its own farm Sadhevana, which I think is really great. It ensures sustainability and quality control which is crucial when dealing with natural ingredients.

I highly recommend you check out this aloe gel even if you’re not an avid user, it’s a great one to have in your kit! And it helps that this comes in 2 sizes so you can find your pick :)

#skincarewithsadhev

I have been using the the newest launch to the L’Oreal Paris Crystal Range, the Crystal Gel Cream for while now and really like it! It’s powered by Salicylic acid that mildly exfoliates and leaves behind Crystal Clear Skin. It goes 10 layers deep and refines pores. The texture is extremely lightweight and absorbs quickly leaving behind no sticky residue. Highly recommend trying it out!

latestIgtvVideos.title: Testing the Ozone Signature Biphasic Makeup Remover
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
AD|

Hey guys, welcome to my IGTV! I never thought I’d be here but well, now I am 😋

@ozonesignature sent across their Biphasic makeup remover to me sometime back and it left me impressed!

It is an oil-inflused formula, the kind I prefer because oils are great at dissolving makeup and my dry skin enjoys the soft feeling afterwards.
I wore a full face of makeup to test this out and it came through👏🏻 Removed everything including my gel liner and mascara without any effort.
Even my matte long stay liquid lip color came off pretty smoothly.

The packaging is travel friendly since it mists out and does not dispense like a liquid but for the same reason, you have to mist it a few extra times to soak the cotton. Not a deal breaker though.

It has some great ingredients like Aloe Vera, Vitamin E along with Jojoba oil and Lavender Essential oil, all of which are good for the skin and senses.
I personally don’t have any sensitivity to essential oils but if your skin is sensitive, a patch test is recommended.

Not much else to say since you can see it for yourself in action here :)

The one thing I really envy our ancestors for is that they grew up in a very clean environment - my grandmother’s skin is still so lit and spotless while my hyperpigmentation is off the charts. The oxidative damage is just so aggressive now that skin is always facing some inflammation thereby resulting in premature ageing, cutely called ‘Inflammaging’. I’m not making this up, there’s legit research her🙃
And that’s why this mist ‘inbalance’ by @dyou.co is actually a great addition to have in your kit!
It has a lovelyyy milky texture that is very hydrating & also moisturising , gives a glow but also works on the ongoing damage, inflammation & oxidative stress skin is facing making it such a great all-rounder.
It also checks bacterial activity on skin so less incidences of acne & so it’s a permanent in my gym bag . I also took it with me recently on a desert vacation where I knew the sun was going to be very strong. It kept my skin so calm! I’m quite obsessed with it also coz its ingredient list is so different from everything else I have. 
You should def try it out!

Dry shampoo is such a gift to this generation yet so many use it the wrong way🥲
The video is self-explanatory but a few pointers:
• Shaking the can is a must. I shook the can but unfortunately that part didn’t get recorded so you can’t see it in the video.
• Don’t spray too close cz that’ll increase the residue & reduce the surface area.
• Spray right onto the scalp and wait for minimum 30 seconds before you start to work in around.
• Using a blow dryer also dusts excess off and adds volume. But if you don’t have the time, you can skip it- not a mandate.
• Avoid touching the brush on the scalp as that can trigger the oils. Stick to the length of the hair.

* * this is a temporary fix and will buy you a day, max 2 depending on the weather. 
For reference, I’m using @livingproofinc Dry Shampoo
.

I’m not a makeup artist and that’s why I love smokey eyes - there is so much room for error. All you need are the right products, good tools and some confidence 🤣
For me, nothing beats smouldering bronze smokey eyes and I finally cracked it this time in the easiest way possible.

The Process:
▶️ Light brown shadow applied all over lid and a little beyond the crease and outer eye. No precision needed.
▶️ Dark brown eyeshadow packed near the lash line center of the lid, blended on top of the lid and also a little intense towards outer corner. 
▶️ Same shadow below the waterline.
▶️ Bronze shadow stick applied majorly on inner & centre of the lid, avoiding the outer corner. Also apply below the waterline.
▶️ Brown Kajal/crayon as eyeliner and Kajal.
▶️ Mascara 

The products:
@toofacedlovesindia Natural Nudes eyeshadow Palette
@byterryofficial Ombré Blackstar eyeshadow in ‘Bronze Moon’
@byterryofficial Crayon Kohl in Matte Mokka (brown Kajal, you can use any) 

Tools:
@elfcosmetics Flawless Concealer brush
@maccosmeticsindia eyeshadow brush 217S
@paccosmetic 208 Blending Eyeshadow brush
